data.text:
The 1888 Society celebrates the founding of the University of Minnesota Law School in 1888 and the future of Minnesota Law made possible by the generous individuals who have created a lasting legacy by including the Law School in their estate or financial plans. Their investment strengthens and builds upon our mission to train the next generation of world-class leaders and visionaries.

Members of the 1888 Society receive a host of benefits that include:
